<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>The update for linux issued as DSA-3426-1 and DSA-3434-1 to address
<a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2015-8543">CVE-2015-8543</a>
uncovered a bug in ctdb, a clustered database to store
temporary data, leading to broken clusters. Updated packages are now
available to address this problem.</p>

<p>For the oldstable distribution (wheezy), this problem has been fixed
in version 1.12+git20120201-5.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (jessie), this problem has been fixed in
version 2.5.4+debian0-4+deb8u1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your ctdb packages.</p>
</define-tag>

